# Figma Component Binding Rule

When creating or editing Figma components, do not use resolved/hardcoded visual values.

## Binding Requirements (Mandatory)

1. Create components with variable bindings, not resolved values.
2. Use existing text styles from the file; no manual typography values.
3. Reject output if any fill/stroke/spacing/radius is unbound.
4. Return a validation list showing which variable/style is bound on each element.

## What Is Forbidden

- Hardcoded color values (hex/rgb) when an existing color variable exists.
- Manual font family/size/weight/line-height when an existing text style exists.
- Manual spacing or corner radius when spacing/radius variables exist.
- Delivering components without a binding audit.

## Required Validation Output

After every Figma component task, return a compact audit like:

- Element: `SignIn/Card` -> Fill: `Background/Raised`, Stroke: `Stroke/Weak`, Radius: `Corner radius/16`
- Element: `SignIn/Title` -> Text Style: `<style-name>`, Color: `Text/Strong`
- Element: `SignIn/PrimaryButton` -> Fill: `Fill/Brand strong`, Text Style: `<style-name>`, Radius: `Corner radius/8`

If any binding cannot be applied, stop and report exactly which token/style is missing.
